task.summary: Fixed issue with error handling on ConnectionManager where the $error variable was being used by $error() by mistake.
Fixed issue with API Manager response for API Method not implemented so that it returns JSON Updated Version number to correct version from testing

Added config manager and Xml generator classes from Boardies IT Solutions library to be included in this project separately - for users who install the API separately on their own servers Added a logger class to help with debugging issues with the API.
Started rework of processing databases and tables separately in different API calls
ConnectionManager now successfully retrieves table and table definition in two separate API calls instead of 1.

Fixed issue with tunnel JSON data being in incorrect format for the tunnel app Fixed issue so that if the tunnel application is not available a proper response is returned instead of an unhandled exception

Some compatibility issues resolved between the new SSH tunnel plugin application Resolved issue where if the tunnel would fail, it would still attempt to connect to the database - this would result in testing if using a valid localhost mysql login through a tunnel on a remote server with the same login details, if the tunnel failed, the database connection would be made to the local machine instead of the remtoe version without any warning. This has been stopped as it shouldn't attempt to connect to the database without the tunnel if the tunnel is required.
Fixed issue where there a function call was used to get whether or not the fingerprint had been confirmed, but the get function didn't exist.
Fixed some issues with the new C++ plugin. Updated to version 1.3.0.0 ready for testing.
Updated version and logging to print the decrypted post array instead of the encrypted.
Ensured that total rows is not retrieved if it has not been set

Fixed issue where commands like SHOW SLAVE STATUS or SHOW CREATE TABLE tablename wouldn't return anything Fixed issue where if SELECT or SHOW statements weren't in uppercase wouldn't be detected as query returning data
Removed some unnecessary debugging. Ready for open sourcing.
Removed passwords and private key details being shown in the log
